    {
      "recommendationid": "116493598",
      "author": {
        "steamid": "76561198213850936",
        "num_games_owned": 413,
        "num_reviews": 3,
        "playtime_forever": 510,
        "playtime_last_two_weeks": 0,
        "playtime_at_review": 25,
        "last_played": 1657079004
      },
      "language": "english",
      "review": "Do not buy if you plan on using a steering wheel, at least for now. Wheel support is nearly non-existent and it feels like if an arcade racer tried to make it feel realistic but over tuned all the values. However, the controller feels fine. \n*edit* \nAfter the most recent update with physics changes wheel drivability is much better and more fun, however still not on the level of games like carX, Asetto or Forza this is a good change, but there are still other issues, here's a list.\n1. very little to do in the game \n2. navigation is annoying without waypoints or better GPS\n3. cars are locked to pre-customized body kits and all tires are super stretched\n4. input mapping is a chore and very limited  \n5. car Ai is just annoying and ruins driving on the open road with how narrow the roads are \n6. the car damage system only acts as an annoyance towards players and serves no point except to take players money and extend the already grindy progression",
      "timestamp_created": 1654379681,
      "timestamp_updated": 1654400816,
